    <cdata>
      <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>&lt;pre&gt;[Congressional Record Volume 170, Number 127 (Friday, August 2, 2024)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [&lt;a href="https://www.gpo.gov"&gt;www.gpo.gov&lt;/a&gt;]By Mrs. RAMIREZ:H.R. 9284.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article 1, Section 8 of the Constitution of the UnitedStates.The single subject of this legislation is:This legislation would amend the Servicemembers CivilRelief Act (SCRA) to allow service members to consolidate orrefinance federal or private student loan debt they or theyand their spouse jointly incurred before they entered themilitary and continue to benefit from the six percent studentloan interest rate cap to which they are entitled through theSCRA.[Page H4974]&lt;/pre&gt;</constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
    </cdata>
